<HEADLINE>
<P>
LIBRARY: 'SALAD BOWL' ANALOGY FOR MODERN LIFE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 After I read the article, "Accusations of Racism Plague Monterey Park Library 
Board" on July 28, I was totally appalled. The American dream is not dead for 
anyone coming to this country in search of better opportunities, but the 
melting pot is no longer an appropriate statement; we are a "salad bowl" where 
each of us is unique and contributes to this society and our communities in 
different ways. 
</P>
<P>
 Unfortunately, (Kathleen) Brzozowski's comments on Marina Tse are so racially 
motivated that it is discouraging for those of us who believe that pluralism 
and diversity are ingredients for a society rich in culture(s). Marina Tse is 
the co-founder of the Multicultural Community Assn. in which all ethnic groups 
work together to promote inter-group relations in our community, and we need 
more committed people like her in our communities.  
</P>
<P>
 ENRIQUE LIMON Alhambra  
</P>
</TEXT>
