<HEADLINE>
<P>
TICKET POLICY CHANGED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CORINNE FLOCKEN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The directors of Adventure City, "The Little Theme Park Just for Kids" that 
opened last Saturday in Stanton, have announced a change in the park's 
admission policy. 
</P>
<P>
 According to co-founder Allan Ansdell Sr., many visitors on opening weekend 
expressed a preference for a pay-as-you-go policy as opposed to the 
single-ticket format originally implemented.So, as of this week, guests have 
two admission options, said Ansdell. 
</P>
<P>
 For $9.95, you can purchase one ticket good for unlimited access to the 
two-acre park's rides, attractions and entertainment. Or, you can pay $1.95 for 
admission to the park and live shows, then purchase separate tickets for each 
ride. A dozen tickets costs $5 and most rides require two to three tickets 
each, said Ansdell. 
</P>
<P>
 Also, when the park opened, children under 2 were admitted free. The new 
policy is that kids under 1 will be admitted free. For hours and other 
information, call (714) 236-9300. CORINNE FLOCKEN 
</P>
