<HEADLINE>
<P>
DUNES: RESTORATION PROVIDES THE REAL JOY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 I was sad to see the article about the destruction of the El Segundo Dunes 
(July 31, page 3) by a "joy rider" and the response of Mr. Ward in the letters 
section (Aug. 11). 
</P>
<P>
 The Dunes Restoration program has been one of the best-run and most fun 
programs I've ever volunteered for in Los Angeles.Every three weeks Rhapsody in 
Green would call us and entertain us while we worked with their great jokes and 
good humor. Dr. Rudi Mattori would bring in local experts to provide scientific 
lectures, and then we all pulled together to weed and replant. Many times we 
would come across fascinating native species that have survived in this area. 
Volunteers ranged from college and high school students to families to singles 
from all parts of the city. I hope this program keeps going, and that the 
off-road "joy rider" and Mr. Ward could join us just one time and see the real 
joy of the El Segundo Dunes. 
</P>
<P>
 KATHY KNIGHT Santa Monica  
</P>
</TEXT>
