<HEADLINE>
<P>
WEST HOLLYWOOD: PRAISE FOR CITY COUNCIL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 I would like to thank and congratulate the West Hollywood City Council on 
their recent deliberations on social service program spending for the next 
fiscal year. 
</P>
<P>
 While under immense pressure and frustration, they performed with eloquence 
and perseverance; perseverance in maintaining current levels of commitment to 
the many essential organizations and programs that serve the residents of West 
Hollywood. 
</P>
<P>
 I am particularly grateful to see my tax dollars go to such organizations as 
Project Angel Food, AID for AIDS and various senior programs whose work we 
could hardly live without. While government on higher levels seems to 
accomplish less and less as each budget is deliberated, I am satisfied that 
this council has made its social commitment to the residents of West Hollywood 
a sacred entity. 
</P>
<P>
 I do not often compliment the council on their actions, but I would like to 
thank Mayor Abbe Land, Pro-Tem John Hellman and council members Paul Koretz, 
Steve Martin and Sal Guarriello for a job well done. 
</P>
<P>
 JOHN UNDERWOOD West Hollywood  
</P>
</TEXT>
