<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS: HARBOR AREA; RETROFITTING OF 4 BRIDGES TO BEGIN IN NOVEMBER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By SUSAN WOODWARD 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Four bridges that link communities in the harbor area will be retrofitted in a 
$5.8-million state Department of Transportation project. 
</P>
<P>
 The bridges are Hobson Avenue Bridge, which crosses Pacific Coast Highway in 
Wilmington; Wilmington Bridge, which crosses the highway in Long Beach; Channel 
Street Bridge, which crosses the Harbor Freeway near San Pedro, and Terminal 
Island Bridge, which crosses the Terminal Island Freeway on Terminal Island. 
</P>
<P>
 The projects will bring the bridges up to earthquake safety standards, said 
Caltrans spokesman Rick Holland. 
</P>
<P>
 Steel supports enclosed with steel casings will be built on the bridge 
columns, Holland said, and foundations will be enlarged. 
</P>
<P>
 Construction is expected to start in November and will take about 11 months. 
SUSAN WOODWARD 
</P>
