<HEADLINE>
<P>
WEST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: VENTURA; HAZARDOUS MATERIAL SCARE CLOSES OFF SITE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By GREG RIPPEE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Ventura fire officials Wednesday briefly barricaded off an area north of 
Buenaventura Golf Course after a sanitation worker discovered an abandoned 
barrel of what was feared to be hazardous material. 
</P>
<P>
 Authorities later determined that the 55-gallon drum at 5700 Olivas Park Drive 
contained little more than oil, solvents and other similar materials. 
</P>
<P>
 Still, they closed a portion of Olivas Park Drive and Seaborg Avenue from 7:35 
a.m. to about 10 a.m., Battalion Chief Roger Morgenthaler of the Ventura Fire 
Department said. 
</P>
<P>
 No evacuations were necessary, although traffic to the adjacent light 
industrial area -- as well as contestants in a Wednesday golf tournament -- had 
to be rerouted, Morgenthaler said. 
</P>
<P>
 Steve Rust, an assistant pro at the city-owned golf course, said the 127 
golfers in the tournament experienced only minor inconvenience. GREG RIPPEE 
</P>
</TEXT>
