<HEADLINE>
<P>
COUNTYWIDE FOCUS: MOTORCYCLISTS REV UP FOR BENEFIT RIDE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JOANNA M. MILLER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 About 2,000 motorcyclists are expected to participate Sunday in the Lorenzo 
Lamas Second Annual "Ride for Life" from Newhall to Lake Casitas. 
</P>
<P>
 Lamas, the star of "Renegade" on Fox TV, will lead the ride, which begins at 
10 a.m. at Valencia Plaza, 24508 Lyons Ave., Newhall, winds along California 
126 and up through the Ojai Valley on California 150 before arriving at the 
lake 70 miles away. 
</P>
<P>
 Cyclists pay $30 per person to participate in the ride, which includes a 
barbecue lunch with live music and entertainment at the lake. Profits go to the 
World Children's Transplant Fund, which provides donor organs for children. 
</P>
<P>
 Entertainment includes Lamas' TV sidekick, Brandscombe Richmond, and his band, 
the Renegade Posse. A second set will be performed by Texas Flood. Comedians 
will also be on hand, along with Ojai-area vendors selling everything from food 
to motorcycle paraphernalia. 
</P>
<P>
 Organizers encourage those interested to sign up in advance, as the 2,000 
slots for the event may sell out, said Dana Tkac, ride coordinator and 
executive director of the World Children's Fund. 
</P>
<P>
 If slots are still available, participants can register from 8 to 10 a.m. the 
morning of the ride at the starting site. 
</P>
<P>
 For more information or to receive a registration form by fax, call (818) 
905-9283. JOANNA M. MILLER 
</P>
</TEXT>
