<HEADLINE>
<P>
DIANE COURTNEY ANDERSON DIES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Diane Courtney Anderson, who assisted with public relations and volunteer work 
for numerous charitable organizations in Orange County, has died of a long 
illness. She was 65. 
</P>
<P>
 Mrs. Anderson worked at Rockwell International in Anaheim for 29 years as 
community affairs manager. In that position, she became well known among the 
county's private nonprofit organizations as a volunteer and board member. 
</P>
<P>
 Those organizations included the American Cancer Society, Saddleback Memorial 
Medical Center, United Way of Orange County and KOCE-TV Citizens Advisory 
Council. 
</P>
<P>
 Mrs. Anderson was a member of the Public Relations Society of America and 
American Management Assn. She was a native Californian. 
</P>
<P>
 Mrs. Anderson is survived by her husband, Roger of Laguna Niguel; daughters, 
Christine Webb of Long Beach and Rebecca Gacek of Menlo Park; mother, Beatrice 
Leib of Florida, and grandchildren, Kirstin, Kileigh and Gavin Hahn. 
</P>
<P>
 Memorial services will be held at 1 p.m. Tuesday at Pacific View Memorial 
Park, 3500 Pacific View Drive, Newport Beach. 
</P>
</TEXT>
