<HEADLINE>
<P>
CLOUDS OF SMOKE TEST SURVIVABILITY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Social Climes complains that "even though they were at . . . outdoor tables, 
that wasn't good enough for their anti-second-hand-smoke neighbors" ("Pushing 
Cigar Smokers to the Very Edge," Aug. 8) 
</P>
<P>
 Tobacco fumes outdoors hang in the air incredibly long! They make me and 
others deathly sick! This is not a matter of power. It is a matter of SURVIVAL! 
</P>
<P>
 JANET N. GRAY, Westchester 
</P>
