<HEADLINE>
<P>
CZECH VICTIMS OF NAZIS WILL BE COMPENSATED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Czech Cabinet on Wednesday approved a gesture to compensate Czechs who 
were held in Nazi concentration camps during World War II. 
</P>
<P>
 The government will give a one-time payment of $82 for every month of 
detention to Czechs imprisoned by the Nazis during the 1938-1945 German 
occupation of Czechoslovakia. The payment will be made to surviving spouses of 
former prisoners who have died but not to their children. 
</P>
</TEXT>
