<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: COUNTYWIDE; GROUP AIDING FOSTER KIDS PLANS BENEFIT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A group that provides services to foster children will hold a fund-raiser next 
month in Newport Beach. 
</P>
<P>
 The event will include a Western barbecue dinner, line dancing and live 
music.A silent auction for trips to Bora Bora, an island in the South Pacific, 
and the Caribbean will also beheld. 
</P>
<P>
 The fund-raiser will take place at 4 p.m. Sept. 10 at the Crean estate, which 
overlooks Upper Newport Bay. Tickets are $75 each. 
</P>
<P>
 The event is sponsored by Advanced Resources for Foster Kids, a nonprofit 
group based in Orange. Advanced Resources provides counseling for foster 
children and foster parents, as well as child care. 
</P>
<P>
 The organization also holds weekend outings and arranges supervised meetings 
between foster children and their natural parents, said Monica Milstead, a 
representative for the group. 
</P>
<P>
 Orange County has about 600 foster families, Milstead said. Advanced Resources 
serves about 20% of them. 
</P>
<P>
 For more information about the fund-raiser, call (714) 978-0340. 
</P>
