<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: COUNTYWIDE; PRESS CLUB TO PRESENT ANNUAL MUSICAL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Orange County Press Club will stage its 11th Gridiron Show 7 p.m. Saturday 
night at the Curtis Theater in Brea. 
</P>
<P>
 The Gridiron Show is a spoof of local politicians and a humorous review of the 
year's past news events. This year's theme is "Late Night with David 
Laventhol," patterned after the David Letterman show. Dave will be played by 
Times correspondent Geoff Boucher. Laventhol is editor at large of Times Mirror 
Co. 
</P>
<P>
 Local journalists make up the cast and will join in an 18-song medley of 
familiar tunes designed to satirize current events. 
</P>
<P>
 Tickets, priced at $10 and $12, are available at the Curtis Theater. Call 
(714) 990-7722. 
</P>
