<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: SANTA ANA; HEALTH FAIR TO OFFER FREE SCREENINGS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JON NALICK 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Thousands of people are expected to receive free health screenings today as 
part of a regional health fair, a spokeswoman said. 
</P>
<P>
 The American Red Cross and private medical professionals will offer free blood 
pressure, vision, dental, prenatal and other health screenings, as well as 
immunizations for children. 
</P>
<P>
 The "Festival Hispano de la Salud," which will also include live entertainment 
for those waiting in line, will be held at Sav-On Drugs at 228 N. Harbor Blvd., 
spokeswoman Oralia Michel said. 
</P>
<P>
 Screenings will be offered from 11 a.m. to 5 p.m. and all children must be 
accompanied by an adult. Children receiving shots must also have their 
immunization records with them, she said.JON NALICK 
</P>
