<HEADLINE>
<P>
GLENDALE / BURBANK FOCUS: GLENDALE; FIRE AT WAREHOUSE PUZZLES OFFICIALS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By STEVE RYFLE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A fire at a Glendale self-storage business Tuesday night destroyed an old 
piano, an ice chest and some other items, but firefighters said the blaze could 
have been far worse if not for a sprinkler system. 
</P>
<P>
 Battalion Chief Mike Carter said fire officials were baffled as to what caused 
the 8:30 p.m. fire at Rene's Van and Storage, 6527 San Fernando Road. 
</P>
<P>
 "We haven't found a logical reason for the fire to start," Carter said. "We're 
not able to identify a source of ignition." 
</P>
<P>
 The 32,000-square-foot warehouse had closed for business at 4 p.m. and was 
empty when the fire was reported, Carter said. Five wooden storage vaults were 
destroyed and several others damaged, but sprinklers kept the fire from 
spreading to other vaults and from damaging the building itself, Carter said. 
</P>
<P>
 "This could have been a much bigger disaster in terms of property loss," he 
said. 
</P>
<P>
 Arson was not strongly suspected in the fire because the items stored in the 
vaults were not particularly valuable, fire officials said. STEVE RYFLE 
</P>
