<P>
BICYCLIST, 64, KILLED IN COLLISION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A 64-year-old man was killed when he unexpectedly turned his bicycle into the 
path of two vehicles on a heavily traveled street, authorities said Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
 Arthur Young of North Hollywood lived at a nearby convalescent home, said Los 
Angeles Police Officer Bill Mulvihill. 
</P>
<P>
 The accident occurred about 2:45 p.m. Tuesday in the 6200 block of Vineland 
Avenue. Young, who was traveling south, abruptly wheeled his bicycle to the 
left, avoiding a car in the lane closest to the curb but steering into the path 
of a van in the fast lane, Mulvihill said. 
</P>
<P>
 He was pronounced dead on arrival at the Medical Center of North Hollywood, 
Mulvihill said. 
</P>
<P>
 The driver of the van was not cited. "There were two vehicles side by side. 
One saw him, the other didn't," Mulvihill said. 
</P>
