<P>
BASEBALL STRIKE: DEVELOPMENTS FROM DAY 13 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Games lost: 14. 
</P>
<P>
 * Total games lost: 169. 
</P>
<P>
 * Games remaining: 500. 
</P>
<P>
 * Total income lost by players: $57.4 million. 
</P>
<P>
 * Estimated revenue lost by owners: $110.5 million. 
</P>
<P>
 * Key development: Players and owners met across the bargaining table for the 
first time since March 19, 1990. 
</P>
<P>
 * In quotes: "We made it pretty clear, our feelings about the (salary) cap. As 
long as it's there, we feel it will be a stumbling block to baseball being 
played the rest of this year, and who knows how long after that." 
</P>
<P>
 -- Paul Molitor, Toronto Blue Jays 
