ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: COSTA MESA; FATAL SHOOTING CASE UNDER INVESTIGATION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By TOM RAGAN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Costa Mesa police detectives Wednesday searched a house in the 800 block of 
Victoria Street, where a 30-year-old woman was found shot to death earlier in 
the week.  
</P>
<P>
 Police Capt. Tom Lazar identified the woman as Roxanne Michelle Martin, 30, of 
Costa Mesa. 
</P>
<P>
 "The case is wide open at this point," Lazar said. "We have no suspects, but 
we're not ruling anybody out. Anybody could be a suspect." 
</P>
<P>
 Police would not say whether Martin lived there, nor how she knew the owner, 
Anthony J. Kubis Jr., 37. Nor would they say whether Kubis lives at the house. 
</P>
<P>
 Martin's body was found Monday, shot several times. 
</P>
<P>
 Police requested a search warrant early Tuesday morning when they could not 
get permission from Kubis to search the house, Lazar said. 
</P>
<P>
 Neighbors who live in the area told police they heard gunshots Monday night 
but didn't take it seriously enough to call police, police spokesman George 
Wilson said. 
</P>
<P>
 One neighbor said she was still afraid because no one has been arrested in the 
slaying. 
</P>
<P>
 "This is the first time anything like this has happened, and I've lived here 
for 19 years," said Marisa Quintana, 19, who lives a block away.TOM RAGAN 
