ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: NEWPORT BEACH; FATHER, SON ARRESTED IN SAILBOAT THEFT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MARK I. PINSKY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A father and son were arrested Wednesday on Lido Isle by Orange County 
sheriff's investigators after the pair boarded a $285,000 sailboat reported 
stolen Saturday in Dana Point Harbor. 
</P>
<P>
 Jaroslaw John Zymny, 48, and Alexander Loren Zymny, 22, who told police their 
last address was in Irvine, were booked at the Orange County Jail on suspicion 
of grand theft and burglary, according to Lt. Dick Olson of the sheriff's 
Harbor Patrol. 
</P>
<P>
 The 43-foot craft Myriah, owned by an Indian Wells man, disappeared from its 
slip in the harbor, police said. At the time of its recovery, Olson said, 
investigators also recovered a 10-foot Avon dinghy tied alongside. The 
inflatable dinghy was reported stolen from Dana Point Harbor at the same time 
as the sailboat, he said. 
</P>
<P>
 Sgt. Paul Falk of the Harbor Patrol described the two men as transients who 
had recently come to the San Clemente area. 
</P>
<P>
 Police credited Todd & Associates, a San Diego-based marine investigation 
firm, with locating the stolen sailboat and contacting the Harbor Patrol. MARK 
I. PINSKY 
</P>
