<P>
MORE OIL-WATER MIX LEAKS REPORTED ON FULLERTON STREET 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Residents of a mile-long stretch of State College Boulevard reported several 
leaks of an oil-water mixture from manhole covers Wednesday, a day after a 
similar spill in the same general area, between Chapman and Commonwealth 
avenues. 
</P>
<P>
 "It's thick, it's not just a light film," said Walt Treadwell, who lives at 
State College and Commonwealth. 
</P>
<P>
 Treadwell said the pressure from the substance below the street pushed the 
manholes loose at three locations, sending what appeared to be hundreds of 
gallons into gutter areas. 
</P>
<P>
 Cleanup crews from the city of Fullerton, the Fullerton Fire Department, 
Unocal and Fullerton Waste Water were on the scene. A spokesman for the Fire 
Department said the cleanup was being handled by Unocal, but a corporate 
spokesman said the line from which the substance came did not belong to them. 
</P>
