<HEADLINE>
<P>
ROAD REDESIGN COMMITTEE IS SEEKING APPLICANTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By LESLIE EARNEST, SPECIAL TO THE TIMES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Residents who want to help redesign Laguna Canyon Road from El Toro Road to 
the San Diego Freeway can apply to be part of a committee being formed for that 
purpose. 
</P>
<P>
 While unwilling to endorse a design preferred by the county that calls for the 
winding road to be moved several hundred yards west of its location, the City 
Council has endorsed widening the road to four lanes and moving it away from 
three area lakes. 
</P>
<P>
 County officials have said they will continue working with the city to try to 
resolve the differences and suggested that the city appoint a five- to 
seven-member committee to consider design alternatives. 
</P>
<P>
 The committee should include people with expertise in road design and 
construction as well as other residents, according to a notice released by the 
city. Members will work with representatives from the city, county and state to 
evaluate design alternatives. 
</P>
<P>
 Interested residents should obtain an application from the city clerk and file 
it by 5 p.m. Sept. 1. Applicants will be interviewed by the City Council on 
Sept. 6 at 6 p.m. in council chambers. 
</P>
<P>
 For more information, call the city clerk's office at (714) 497-0705. 
</P>
