<HEADLINE>
<P>
ROCK 'N THE PUCK WITH STARS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By LAURIE K. SCHENDEN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Well sports fans, this may be the last chance to bid farewell to Kings hockey 
star Luc Robitaille, who was traded this month to Pittsburgh. But what an L.A. 
way to go -- surrounded by celebrities, with the Spin Doctors singing the 
National Anthem.Robitaille will lead a parade of professional and celebrity 
players in the Rock 'N the Puck Celebrity Hockey Game, on the Kings' home ice 
at the Great Western Forum at 7:30 p.m. Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
 Celebrity hockey players include "Wayne's World's" Mike Myers, actors Scott 
Bakula, Dave Coulier, Richard Dean Anderson, Jamie Walters and MTV's Riki 
Rachtman. Among the pro players are the Kings' Rob Blake, Darryl Fydor, Mike 
Donnelly and recently retired Dave Taylor; Pavel Bure of the Vancouver Canucks 
and Chris Chelios of the Chicago Blackhawks. Mark and Brian of radio station 
KLOS will emcee. 
</P>
<P>
 The Spin Doctors will return after the game to perform at the VIP after-game 
party, where you can hobnob and talk pucks with the players for $95.50. General 
admission prices to the game only are $9.55 and $19.55, available at the Forum 
box office or Ticketmaster, (213) 480-3232. 
</P>
<P>
 Funds raised at the benefit, sponsored by KLOS, Iceoplex (the Kings' training 
facility) and Kmart, will go to the T.J. Martell Foundation and Neil Bogart 
Memorial Fund. LAURIE K. SCHENDEN 
</P>
