<P>
 Novell Says It Will Lay Off 1,750: The Utah-based company reported a 
$4-million loss for its third quarter and said it will make the cuts during the 
next six months to ease its financial situation. Novell Inc., which produces 
the best-selling software for linking personal computers in networks, has seen 
costs rise and revenues decline to an extent greater than expected from its 
June purchase of WordPerfect Corp., a maker of word-processing and other PC 
programs.The cutback amounts to about 17% of the combined work force of Novell 
and WordPerfect and follows a reduction of 1,025 workers made at WordPerfect in 
