<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS: CERRITOS; TOWNE CENTER OFFERS GRAND OPENING EVENTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JOHN CANALIS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Cerritos Towne Center's new 40-store retail complex is throwing a three-day 
grand opening this weekend featuring music and free food samples. 
</P>
<P>
 The shopping center, anchored by a Wal-Mart store and Smith's Food & Drug 
Center, will provide about 900 jobs when all 40 businesses are open in October, 
and should provide the city with about $3.5 million in revenue in its first 
year, officials said. 
</P>
<P>
 The city is expected to collect $1.8 million in lease payments and $1.7 
million in sales taxes from the center's developers in the coming year, said 
city spokeswoman Michele Wastal. 
</P>
<P>
 Phoenix-based Vestar Development built the center on 40 acres of city land at 
Bloomfield Avenue and Towne Center Drive. The retail stores are part of a 
125-acre complex that includes a business park, hotel and the Cerritos 
Performing Arts Center. 
</P>
<P>
 The grand opening events are scheduled from 10 a.m. to 9:30 p.m. Friday 
through Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
 A total of 25 stores, including Wal-Mart and Smith's, have already opened. 
JOHN CANALIS 
</P>
</TEXT>
