<TEXT>
<P>
 Prostate research funding -- In an article in Tuesday's editions about the 
Assembly's rejection of a cigarette tax hike to pay for prostate cancer 
research, The Times incorrectly reported that the federal government will spend 
$51 million on such research this year in California. That amount will be spent 
nationwide; California's share is about $3 million, according to the National 
Cancer Institute. 
</P>
